.TH _printf 3 "Holberton" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
_printf \- produce output according to a format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B int _printf(const char *format, ...);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B _printf()
function writes output to the standard output stream according to a
.BR printf (3)
style format string. Supported conversion specifiers include:
.BR c ,
.BR s ,
.BR % ,
.BR d ,
.BR i ,
.BR u ,
.BR o ,
.BR x ,
.BR X ,
.B b
(binary),
.B p
(pointer),
.B S
(string with non printable characters as \\xXX),
.B r
(reverse),
and
.B R
(ROT13).
For non\-custom specifiers, the following features are handled:
flags
.BR + ,
space,
.BR # ,
.BR 0 ,
.BR \- ;
field width and precision; and length modifiers
.BR l
and
.BR h
for
.BR d , i , u , o , x , X .
Output uses an internal 1024\-byte buffer to reduce write calls.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Upon success,
.B _printf()
returns the number of characters printed. On error, \-1 is returned.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR printf (3)
.SH AUTHORS
Ghaida A. (GitHub: GhaidaAL36)
